<br>
Also, I believe that there is evidence of tropical forests such as the Amazon being around for tens of thousands of years (they are too close to the equator to be glaciated) - a crust role recent enough to be &quot;remembered&quot; by the Egyptians (I'm assuming an absolute max of about 20 or 30 thousand years here) should curtail the age of these ecosystems to less than their known age.<br>
<br>
